Twenty-five Civil Society Organisations (CSO) have hailed the Osun State government for administering the state in a way that deliver dividends of democracy and good governance to its residents. Comrade Declan Ihekaire, at a news conference after a two-day projects assessment tour, said the tour was part of their nationwide good governance assessment tour of various government intervention projects and programmes.   Lagos spends N23b to upgrade education infrastructure     Oyo Assembly set to determine deputy governor’s fate     Adamu to campaign council: Osun is a must-win   He said the tour was to collate the needs of the people, and their expectations from the government. Ihekaire said: “We are impressed that the projects are based on the need of the people, according to their peculiar demands. Governments mainly exist to cater for the need of the people and as such, must at all times, prioritise their welfare. “The current administration in Osun State, from our interaction with the people, particularly government workers in various categories, has given serious attention to the welfare of civil servants and every persons working with the government and its structures.”